{%- comment -%}
  Vivid — Our Sourcing (Ritual "Made Traceable" pattern, tailored for SA).
  Renders ingredient → supplier → manufacturing location, plus the COA promise.
  Data is editable in section settings so the team can add new ingredients
  without touching code.
{%- endcomment -%}

<section class="sourcing-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Made Traceable in South Africa</p>
    <h1>Every ingredient, every supplier, every batch.</h1>
    <p class="lede">Most supplement brands won't tell you where their actives come from. We will. Below is every ingredient currently in a Vivid bottle, the country it's grown or extracted in, and the lab in Centurion that tests every batch before it ships.</p>
    <div class="sourcing-promise">
      <div class="promise-item">
        <strong>Exact mg labelled</strong>
        <span>No proprietary blends. The number on the bottle is the number in the capsule.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="promise-item">
        <strong>Third-party batch tested</strong>
        <span>Identity, potency and heavy metals — by an ISO 17025-aligned SA lab.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="promise-item">
        <strong>SAHPRA-aligned</strong>
        <span>Regulated formulations meet South African complementary-medicine standards.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
.sourcing-grid{border:1px solid var(--cream,#EEE5D2);border-radius:14px;overflow:hidden;background:var(--paper,#FBF7EE)}
.sourcing-grid .srow{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1.3fr 1fr 1.2fr 1.4fr .7fr;gap:16px;padding:14px 18px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--cream,#EEE5D2);font-size:14.5px;align-items:center}
.sourcing-grid .srow:last-child{border-bottom:none}
.sourcing-grid .srow.head{background:var(--bone,#F4EEE2);font-weight:600;font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--moss,#466B4F)}
.sourcing-grid .srow .ingredient{font-weight:600}
.sourcing-grid .srow a{color:var(--forest,#1F3D2E);font-weight:600}
@media(max-width:749px){
  .sourcing-grid .srow{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:6px 14px;padding:14px 16px}
  .sourcing-grid .srow.head{display:none}
  .sourcing-grid .srow .ingredient{grid-column:1/-1;font-size:16px}
}
</style>
<section class="sourcing-table">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="sourcing-head">
      <h2>Ingredient sourcing map</h2>
      <p>Updated quarterly. Last updated <strong>{{ section.settings.updated_label | default: 'June 2026' }}</strong>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sourcing-grid">
      <div class="srow head">
        <span>Ingredient</span>
        <span>Source country</span>
        <span>Supplier</span>
        <span>Form / standardisation</span>
        <span>COA</span>
      </div>
      {%- for block in section.blocks -%}
        {%- if block.type == 'ingredient' -%}
          <div class="srow" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
            <span class="ingredient">{{ block.settings.name }}</span>
            <span>{{ block.settings.country }}</span>
            <span>{{ block.settings.supplier }}</span>
            <span>{{ block.settings.form }}</span>
            <span>
              {%- if block.settings.coa_url != blank -%}
                <a href="{{ block.settings.coa_url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View PDF</a>
              {%- else -%}
                On request
              {%- endif -%}
            </span>
          </div>
        {%- endif -%}
      {%- endfor -%}
    </div>
    <p class="sourcing-footnote">Don't see an ingredient listed? It hasn't been audited for this page yet. Email <a href="mailto:sourcing@vividhealth.co.za">sourcing@vividhealth.co.za</a> and we'll send the documentation.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sourcing-process">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="process-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Our four-stage testing</p>
        <h2>How a Vivid batch gets to your shelf.</h2>
        <ol class="process-steps">
          <li><strong>1 · Raw material identity</strong><br>Every shipment is checked against a reference standard before it touches a capsule. FT-IR + HPLC where applicable.</li>
          <li><strong>2 · Potency assay</strong><br>The active is measured. The label number has to match the lab number, or the batch doesn't run.</li>
          <li><strong>3 · Heavy metals + microbial</strong><br>Lead, arsenic, mercury, cadmium plus total plate count, yeast, mould, E. coli, salmonella.</li>
          <li><strong>4 · Finished-product retest</strong><br>After encapsulation, we re-test a random sample of the finished bottle. Only then does the batch release.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
      <div class="process-card">
        <p class="eyebrow">If we ever miss the mark</p>
        <h3>Money back. No questions, 30 days.</h3>
        <p>If a Vivid product doesn't do what we said it would, send it back — full refund, including shipping. We carry the risk, not you.</p>
        <a href="/pages/shipping-and-returns" class="btn ghost">Read the returns policy →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Sourcing — Made Traceable",
  "tag": "section",
  "settings": [
    { "type": "text", "id": "updated_label", "label": "Updated label", "default": "June 2026" }
  ],
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "ingredient",
      "name": "Ingredient row",
